ğŸ“‚ Repository Structure

The repository is organized into the following directories:

Folder	Description
Control_Flow_Statements	Programs demonstrating loops, conditionals, and branching statements.
Input and Output (I & O)	Examples of Java input/output using Scanner, BufferedReader, etc.
Methods	Programs illustrating method creation, calling, overloading, and recursion.
OOPs	Object-Oriented Programming examples covering classes, objects, inheritance, polymorphism, encapsulation, and abstraction.
Pattern Printing	Programs for generating various patterns using loops.
Programs	Miscellaneous Java programs and exercises.
Recursion/ Codes	Recursive algorithms and practice problems.
Static	Examples showing the use of static variables, methods, and blocks.
TypeCasting	Programs demonstrating typecasting and conversions in Java.
